{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The fast GP-MPC implementation supports arbitrary GPyTorch [39] (approximate) GP models, as well as data processing strategies for online-learning applications, which are demonstrated in simulation and hardware on the automotive miniature racing platform CRS [40].",
    "Last, L4acados is used to implement a GP-MPC motion controller for an ISO lane change maneuver with a full-scale autonomous vehicle.",
    "We are concerned with real-time optimal control of nonlinear dynamical systems of the formx(t + 1) = f (x(t), u(t)) + B d g tr (x(t), u(t)) + w(t),(1)where x(t) ∈ R nx denotes the state of the system, u(t) ∈ R nu, the applied control input, and w(t) ∈ R nx, process noise.",
    "The ground-truth dynamics are split into a known, nominal part of the system dynamics, f: R nx×nu → R nx, and an unknown residual, g tr: R nx×nu → R ng.",
    "The residual affects certain components of the full state through the matrix B d ∈ R nx×ng, which is assumed to have full column rank."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The fast GP-MPC implementation supports arbitrary GPyTorch [39] (approximate) GP models, as well as data processing strategies for online-learning applications, which are demonstrated in simulation and hardware on the automotive miniature racing platform CRS [40]."
  ]
